WEBVTT

1
00:02:29.400 --> 00:02:30.485
What?

2
00:02:35.698 --> 00:02:37.075
I can't understand.

3
00:02:48.503 --> 00:02:49.503
Speak plainly.

4
00:02:55.718 --> 00:02:58.763
Stop. Stop it.

5
00:03:30.920 --> 00:03:32.280
There's been a raven.

6
00:03:37.301 --> 00:03:38.719
Good morrow. Your Grace.

7
00:03:40.179 --> 00:03:42.223
Slept well. I trust?

8
00:03:42.974 --> 00:03:45.059
As I said. there's been a raven.

9
00:03:48.146 --> 00:03:51.524
Aegon's army departed King's Landing
a fortnight ago.

10
00:03:51.607 --> 00:03:56.404
The castles of Rosby and Stokeworth
have both fallen without siege.

11
00:03:56.487 --> 00:03:58.739
They have raised Aegon's banner

12
00:03:58.823 --> 00:04:02.076
and added their levies
to Ser Criston Cole's host.

13
00:04:03.202 --> 00:04:04.912
Both houses cited that

14
00:04:05.955 --> 00:04:09.333
sad business with the usurper's son
in their declarations.

15
00:04:10.585 --> 00:04:12.128
Ser Criston's army.

16
00:04:12.962 --> 00:04:14.547
now tripled in strength.

17
00:04:15.381 --> 00:04:17.467
might have Harrenhal as its destination.

18
00:04:18.342 --> 00:04:21.512
Even if you can raise a host of Rivermen.

19
00:04:21.596 --> 00:04:24.098
they will not be ready in time
to face him.

20
00:04:30.813 --> 00:04:33.107
Let's see
what your lord paramount is made of.

21
00:04:39.405 --> 00:04:43.493
My... My... My... My prince...
Uh. my Grace. Your Grace.

22
00:04:45.036 --> 00:04:48.247
Lord Grover is looking more hale
and healthy than I expected.

23
00:04:48.331 --> 00:04:50.791
Uh. this is Oscar Tully.
grandson to Grover Tully.

24
00:04:50.875 --> 00:04:55.087
He is heir to Riverrun and the future
Lord Paramount of the Riverlands.

25
00:04:55.713 --> 00:04:59.175
His Grace. the King Consort.
Daemon Targaryen.

26
00:04:59.258 --> 00:05:01.802
- It is an honor. Your Grace.
- Indeed.

27
00:05:08.392 --> 00:05:09.977
How fares your grandsire?

28
00:05:14.398 --> 00:05:16.984
Sadly. he remains incapacitated.

29
00:05:17.735 --> 00:05:20.363
He lies in a kind of waking sleep.

30
00:05:20.446 --> 00:05:23.282
unable to do much more
than take meager drink.

31
00:05:24.075 --> 00:05:25.910
It is barely enough to sustain him.

32
00:05:26.577 --> 00:05:27.912
So he's alive.

33
00:05:28.454 --> 00:05:30.790
Yes. gods be good.

34
00:05:30.873 --> 00:05:33.501
Well. my time is short.
and I have need of an army.

35
00:05:33.584 --> 00:05:35.878
Perhaps you might place
a feather pillow over his head

36
00:05:35.962 --> 00:05:38.089
and speed along your inheritance.

37
00:05:40.216 --> 00:05:43.844
I... I love my grandsire like a father.

38
00:05:44.637 --> 00:05:47.974
My own lord father died suddenly.
himself a young man.

39
00:05:48.891 --> 00:05:51.394
Lord Grover raised me in his stead.

40
00:05:51.477 --> 00:05:52.853
All very touching.

41
00:05:52.937 --> 00:05:54.939
Are you here to speak
with your grandsire's voice.

42
00:05:55.022 --> 00:05:56.857
for House Tully and the Riverlands?

43
00:05:56.941 --> 00:05:58.401
While he still lives?

44
00:06:01.153 --> 00:06:04.323
- That is not our way.
- Then you are of no use to me.

45
00:06:05.575 --> 00:06:08.661
I can see why the Blackwoods and
the Brackens did not fear to start a war

46
00:06:08.744 --> 00:06:11.038
beneath the nose of their liege lords.

47
00:06:11.122 --> 00:06:13.332
House Tully is a fish with no head.

48
00:06:13.416 --> 00:06:17.253
Remind me which of your countrymen
claim to fight in the name of Aegon.

49
00:06:17.336 --> 00:06:19.630
Was it Bracken or Blackwood?

50
00:06:19.714 --> 00:06:22.258
It was House Bracken
that declared Green. Your Grace.

51
00:06:22.341 --> 00:06:23.467
Who could remember?

52
00:06:24.635 --> 00:06:28.472
Summon the Blackwoods here. I require
men of action to lead my host of Rivermen.

53
00:06:57.585 --> 00:06:58.586
Milady.

54
00:07:02.548 --> 00:07:05.384
"Princess." if we're holding
to formalities.

55
00:07:06.385 --> 00:07:08.596
Apologies. princess.

56
00:07:10.473 --> 00:07:12.350
And you are Alyn.

57
00:07:12.933 --> 00:07:14.644
Yes. princess.

58
00:07:16.395 --> 00:07:19.190
I'm given to understand
my lord husband owes you his life.

59
00:07:23.152 --> 00:07:26.197
But I was not told
his savior was so comely.

60
00:07:27.406 --> 00:07:29.450
Your mother must have been very beautiful.

61
00:07:29.533 --> 00:07:30.576
Rhaenys.

62
00:07:39.752 --> 00:07:41.712
- Is your work finished?
- No. my lord.

63
00:07:53.391 --> 00:07:55.017
I just had a word with your captains.

64
00:07:57.478 --> 00:08:00.815
He was the sailor who plucked you
from your watery grave?

65
00:08:08.406 --> 00:08:09.407
Yes.

66
00:08:10.991 --> 00:08:12.618
You did not think to mention it?

67
00:08:13.661 --> 00:08:15.329
I did not think it relevant.

68
00:08:17.623 --> 00:08:19.375
I know who he is. Corlys.

69
00:08:22.128 --> 00:08:24.255
Alyn's past is no fault of his.

70
00:08:25.631 --> 00:08:28.050
He saved his lord's life.
He should be raised up and honored.

71
00:08:28.134 --> 00:08:30.886
- not hidden beneath the tides.
- Is this why you came?

72
00:08:32.471 --> 00:08:34.223
To subject me to an inquisition?

73
00:08:36.475 --> 00:08:39.687
I came to tell you
that Baela has called me to Dragonstone.

74
00:08:40.271 --> 00:08:41.272
Baela?

75
00:08:42.606 --> 00:08:45.276
That council is going to dine on her
and Jace for supper.

76
00:08:45.359 --> 00:08:47.445
They grow restless in Rhaenyra's absence.

77
00:08:47.528 --> 00:08:48.654
Still.

78
00:08:49.447 --> 00:08:50.865
Where has that woman gone?

79
00:08:50.948 --> 00:08:53.826
I suspect to try
and draw us all back from the abyss.

80
00:09:16.557 --> 00:09:17.933
Good morrow. Your Grace.

81
00:09:18.559 --> 00:09:19.810
Good morrow. grand maester.

82
00:09:23.731 --> 00:09:24.815
As requested.

83
00:09:26.233 --> 00:09:28.736
- I brewed it myself.
- Thank you.

84
00:09:29.862 --> 00:09:31.489
I will see it delivered discreetly.

85
00:09:33.491 --> 00:09:37.578
Do report if the recipient
has need of any remedy.

86
00:09:37.661 --> 00:09:39.914
The tea is known to disagree with the gut.

87
00:09:40.790 --> 00:09:42.416
I shall observe the girl closely.

88
00:09:49.548 --> 00:09:50.549
Grand maester.

89
00:09:57.223 --> 00:10:01.560
You've ever been a practical man.
an honorable servant to the crown.

90
00:10:02.937 --> 00:10:05.439
And you served my lord husband
in his darkest hours.

91
00:10:06.565 --> 00:10:08.150
Such was my duty. Your Grace.

92
00:10:10.236 --> 00:10:11.237
Tell me...

93
00:10:13.656 --> 00:10:16.283
do you believe Viserys wanted Aegon
to succeed him?

94
00:10:21.205 --> 00:10:23.123
I could not know.

95
00:10:25.334 --> 00:10:27.878
His Grace never raised the matter with me.

96
00:11:13.215 --> 00:11:14.466
Ugh!

97
00:11:20.097 --> 00:11:21.181
Ugh!

98
00:11:28.397 --> 00:11:31.158
Ser Criston Cole's host
has taken to exploiting the tree cover

99
00:11:31.191 --> 00:11:32.318
to conceal its movements.

100
00:11:32.401 --> 00:11:35.029
He now only travels by night.
to confound our dragons.

101
00:11:35.112 --> 00:11:36.822
And what is Cole's heading?

102
00:11:37.364 --> 00:11:38.407
It is difficult to say.

103
00:11:38.490 --> 00:11:41.911
but there were signs of an army
moving northwest. I believe.

104
00:11:41.994 --> 00:11:43.329
She believes.

105
00:11:43.412 --> 00:11:45.456
You should have burned them
when you had the chance.

106
00:11:45.539 --> 00:11:48.259
Perhaps you can. Ser Alfred.
when you next sight them on your dragon.

107
00:11:49.460 --> 00:11:53.172
The only reason we know any of this
is because of Baela's efforts.

108
00:11:53.255 --> 00:11:54.840
What do we know. my prince?

109
00:11:54.924 --> 00:11:57.259
If you ask me. it is little and less.

110
00:11:57.343 --> 00:11:59.219
We know that
Cole possesses a host

111
00:11:59.303 --> 00:12:01.388
that is growing in strength
and that it is a problem.

112
00:12:01.472 --> 00:12:04.224
Can Daemon hope to meet it
with his own in time?

113
00:12:04.308 --> 00:12:07.561
And if I know the Riverlands.
he has more disentangling ahead of him

114
00:12:07.645 --> 00:12:10.731
than the end of a Lyseni orgy.

115
00:12:10.814 --> 00:12:13.442
Have you had word from your father?

116
00:12:16.779 --> 00:12:19.782
- No.
- Ravens were sent to Harrenhal.

117
00:12:19.865 --> 00:12:23.494
seeking news of Daemon's progress
with the Riverlords.

118
00:12:23.577 --> 00:12:25.955
None have. as yet. returned.

119
00:12:26.038 --> 00:12:27.498
Just so.

120
00:12:27.581 --> 00:12:30.042
An enemy host. growing in constitution.

121
00:12:30.125 --> 00:12:34.838
marches somewhere
in the vastness of the Crownlands.

122
00:12:34.922 --> 00:12:37.841
We could perhaps act
if only we had a host of our own

123
00:12:38.592 --> 00:12:39.969
or someone here to lead us.

124
00:12:40.594 --> 00:12:42.471
Mind your tongue. Ser Alfred.

125
00:12:43.973 --> 00:12:46.433
Does it speak falsely. my prince?

126
00:12:46.517 --> 00:12:48.978
This council is rudderless.

127
00:12:49.061 --> 00:12:51.146
I'm doing my best to steer it. Ser Alfred.

128
00:12:52.815 --> 00:12:56.443
Why should your voice be any louder
than ours. princess?

129
00:12:56.527 --> 00:12:58.278
The queen did not name you Hand.

130
00:12:58.362 --> 00:13:00.739
It is her voice.
and that of the king consort.

131
00:13:00.823 --> 00:13:04.076
that we need to raise alliances
and command our vassals.

132
00:13:04.159 --> 00:13:07.121
- But they are gone!
- What has come of this council?

133
00:13:12.334 --> 00:13:13.335
My lord.

134
00:13:16.880 --> 00:13:19.675
Our enemy is on the march.

135
00:13:20.342 --> 00:13:22.462
Is there naught to be done
in the absence of the queen

136
00:13:22.511 --> 00:13:25.723
but to grouse and claw for power?

137
00:13:31.729 --> 00:13:33.939
We do not know the queen's doings.

138
00:13:35.315 --> 00:13:39.403
But we must trust that she seeks
the same as each of us at this table.

139
00:13:41.613 --> 00:13:43.407
An end to this conflict.

140
00:13:58.088 --> 00:13:59.548
No prisoners!

141
00:14:05.846 --> 00:14:07.473
Men of House Darklyn.

142
00:14:08.390 --> 00:14:12.478
all who bend the knee to the true king.
Aegon. will be spared.

143
00:14:13.562 --> 00:14:16.231
You can earn back your honor
by raising his banner

144
00:14:16.315 --> 00:14:20.402
and fighting in his name
against the Whore of Dragonstone.

145
00:14:21.320 --> 00:14:23.155
All who refuse...

146
00:14:25.157 --> 00:14:26.492
will have their death.

147
00:14:41.215 --> 00:14:42.841
Good morrow. Lord Darklyn.

148
00:14:43.634 --> 00:14:46.386
Is there no honor left
in this world. Cole?

149
00:14:47.054 --> 00:14:51.100
Sacking your queen's own castles
and putting her people to the sword?

150
00:14:52.017 --> 00:14:53.268
"Kingmaker."

151
00:14:57.940 --> 00:15:00.317
You're not fit for the white cloak.

152
00:15:03.779 --> 00:15:06.323
This is a better death
than a traitor deserves.

153
00:15:07.366 --> 00:15:08.700
You should thank me for it.

154
00:15:11.745 --> 00:15:14.164
Yours will come in kind.

155
00:15:29.179 --> 00:15:30.222
Lord Hand.

156
00:15:45.904 --> 00:15:47.614
We'll lead the van northeast.

157
00:15:48.323 --> 00:15:49.366
Follow the coastline.

158
00:15:51.076 --> 00:15:52.828
I realize you were neither born nor bred

159
00:15:52.911 --> 00:15:55.330
anywhere near the Crownlands.
my good Lord Hand.

160
00:15:56.123 --> 00:15:58.208
but Harrenhal is to the west.

161
00:16:02.629 --> 00:16:03.755
Indeed. it is.

162
00:16:07.176 --> 00:16:08.302
<i>Fuck you.</i>

163
00:16:08.844 --> 00:16:11.722
I told you we should've sent our dragons
and now look what's happened.

164
00:16:12.681 --> 00:16:15.434
Daemon. of all people.
has taken Harrenhal.

165
00:16:15.517 --> 00:16:17.936
I give you a job
and now you just sit there.

166
00:16:18.020 --> 00:16:19.563
It's your fucking castle!

167
00:16:22.232 --> 00:16:25.694
Well. that castle is more crippled
than I am. Your Grace.

168
00:16:27.613 --> 00:16:30.508
It's like to drive Daemon to
madness as he attempts to make use of it.

169
00:16:30.532 --> 00:16:32.201
It is beyond his faculties.

170
00:16:33.535 --> 00:16:38.207
It is also penniless. as I happily
control all of its gold. so...

171
00:16:38.999 --> 00:16:41.001
As Harrenhal saps Daemon's resolve.

172
00:16:41.084 --> 00:16:43.587
the false queen remains trapped
on her island.

173
00:16:43.670 --> 00:16:46.924
and Ser Criston continues felling castles
in the Crownlands.

174
00:16:47.007 --> 00:16:48.634
Uh... Well I...

175
00:16:49.551 --> 00:16:53.764
I need to be informed of these things.
if I am to make informed rulings.

176
00:16:53.847 --> 00:16:56.600
I will not be made to look a fool
in front of my allies and enemies.

177
00:16:56.683 --> 00:16:58.393
Harrenhal must wait.

178
00:17:02.022 --> 00:17:04.358
Ser Criston is marching on Rook's Rest.

179
00:17:05.192 --> 00:17:07.486
Rook's...? A pathetic prize.
I gave no such command.

180
00:17:07.569 --> 00:17:09.071
The castle is small.

181
00:17:10.280 --> 00:17:11.573
weakly defended.

182
00:17:11.657 --> 00:17:14.660
and Lord Staunton sits
on Rhaenyra's council.

183
00:17:14.743 --> 00:17:19.248
After Cole smashes it. we'll have
Dragonstone effectively cut off by land.

184
00:17:20.958 --> 00:17:23.085
This war will not be won
with dragons alone.

185
00:17:23.752 --> 00:17:26.755
but with dragons flying
behind armies of men.

186
00:17:26.838 --> 00:17:30.467
No. Have him turn about.
I want Harrenhal back.

187
00:17:31.843 --> 00:17:33.804
Cole is already preparing his attack.

188
00:17:35.722 --> 00:17:37.474
Uh. how... How do you know this?

189
00:17:37.557 --> 00:17:39.101
He sent word to me.

190
00:17:40.519 --> 00:17:41.520
To you?

191
00:17:44.648 --> 00:17:45.983
The two of you have been...

192
00:17:47.484 --> 00:17:48.485
plotting

193
00:17:49.486 --> 00:17:51.238
without my authority?

194
00:18:12.509 --> 00:18:13.552
Mm.

195
00:18:47.210 --> 00:18:48.210
Mm.

196
00:18:54.092 --> 00:18:55.927
Harrenhal is a useful morass.

197
00:18:56.470 --> 00:18:59.306
It will keep Daemon well-occupied
while we strengthen our host

198
00:18:59.389 --> 00:19:01.600
and weaken Rhaenyra's support
on the mainland.

199
00:19:01.683 --> 00:19:03.810
We'll deal with it
and the Riverlands in time.

200
00:19:04.728 --> 00:19:05.729
But right now.

201
00:19:06.355 --> 00:19:10.108
Rook's Rest is an easy target
and a worthy effort.

202
00:19:12.069 --> 00:19:14.613
Don't you agree. my king?

203
00:19:30.003 --> 00:19:31.004
Come.

204
00:19:35.217 --> 00:19:36.218
Lord Larys.

205
00:19:40.931 --> 00:19:45.477
I thought I'd look in on you. Your Grace.
after your absence from the Small Council.

206
00:19:46.144 --> 00:19:48.021
I feared something was amiss.

207
00:19:49.189 --> 00:19:53.693
You're kind to do so. my lord.
But indulgence was my sin.

208
00:19:53.777 --> 00:19:58.198
I ventured into the lamprey pie
at last night's supper. Too far. I fear.

209
00:20:01.993 --> 00:20:02.993
Mm.

210
00:20:05.247 --> 00:20:07.124
That is a rich indulgence.

211
00:20:09.000 --> 00:20:11.670
But I believe it is a sin
to deny your appetites.

212
00:20:12.295 --> 00:20:15.090
They are what make us fully alive
as mortal men.

213
00:20:19.845 --> 00:20:22.222
Was anything of note discussed
at the council?

214
00:20:22.305 --> 00:20:26.893
Daemon having seized Harrenhal
and His Grace's resulting displeasure.

215
00:20:26.977 --> 00:20:29.729
I would have thought
you would be the most aggrieved. my lord.

216
00:20:31.940 --> 00:20:33.900
I see it as a loss for our greater good.

217
00:20:35.694 --> 00:20:38.238
Dragonstone's attentions
are greatly divided.

218
00:20:38.321 --> 00:20:41.241
First in the Riverlands and the Gullet.
and now the Crownlands.

219
00:20:42.367 --> 00:20:44.411
Ser Criston wins every challenge
he faces there.

220
00:20:44.494 --> 00:20:47.247
That truth alone is like
to incite Rhaenyra's fury.

221
00:20:48.498 --> 00:20:50.667
He's covered himself in glory.
to be sure.

222
00:20:52.210 --> 00:20:53.753
You must worry for him.

223
00:20:54.880 --> 00:20:57.132
Your sworn sword...

224
00:20:58.508 --> 00:21:01.428
on the march. ever exposed to dragons.

225
00:21:01.511 --> 00:21:03.138
It is a perilous road.

226
00:21:06.850 --> 00:21:08.560
Ser Criston is the Hand of the king.

227
00:21:10.187 --> 00:21:12.355
We should all pray for his victory
and safe return.

228
00:21:13.857 --> 00:21:14.900
Indeed.

229
00:21:24.951 --> 00:21:27.746
If I may be so bold. my queen...

230
00:21:34.127 --> 00:21:35.921
You have not seemed yourself of late.

231
00:21:38.131 --> 00:21:42.135
Only weeks ago. my lord husband was alive
and the realm was at peace.

232
00:21:43.011 --> 00:21:47.641
Now I've barely had the hours to grieve
one tragedy before suffering the next.

233
00:21:47.724 --> 00:21:50.644
I regret if I have not been myself.

234
00:21:53.563 --> 00:21:54.606
Hm.

235
00:21:55.148 --> 00:21:57.734
I did not know you shared
your lord husband's love

236
00:21:58.818 --> 00:22:00.111
for the histories.

237
00:22:02.030 --> 00:22:05.075
If not his love.
then certainly an abiding interest.

238
00:22:06.910 --> 00:22:08.620
The voice of history guided Viserys.

239
00:22:08.703 --> 00:22:11.623
He knew that his wisdom alone
could only reach so far.

240
00:22:11.706 --> 00:22:14.042
Do you think
that is why he changed his mind...

241
00:22:15.877 --> 00:22:16.878
in the end?

242
00:22:18.547 --> 00:22:23.260
No matter how suited he thought
Rhaenyra for the crown. the. uh...

243
00:22:24.052 --> 00:22:26.555
voices of history. as you say.

244
00:22:27.138 --> 00:22:30.475
would have told him how the realm
would react to her succession.

245
00:22:30.559 --> 00:22:33.520
It's impossible to know what steered
his thoughts in those final hours.

246
00:22:35.522 --> 00:22:37.274
Do you now doubt his intentions?

247
00:22:45.532 --> 00:22:47.742
Rhaenyra's supporters will believe
what they wish.

248
00:22:48.702 --> 00:22:50.036
And so will Aegon's.

249
00:22:51.580 --> 00:22:54.833
The war will be fought. many will die...

250
00:22:56.084 --> 00:22:58.253
and the victor will eventually
ascend the throne.

251
00:23:00.630 --> 00:23:03.550
The significance
of Viserys's intentions died with him.

252
00:23:10.390 --> 00:23:11.641
Yes. it did.

253
00:24:49.072 --> 00:24:51.783
It's a touch late
to be stalking about a strange castle.

254
00:24:51.866 --> 00:24:54.828
- putting its people to the sword.
- You.

255
00:24:56.454 --> 00:24:57.872
I'm called Alys.

256
00:24:58.998 --> 00:24:59.999
Strong?

257
00:25:00.500 --> 00:25:01.501
Rivers.

258
00:25:02.669 --> 00:25:03.670
A bastard.

259
00:25:04.295 --> 00:25:06.756
Once you get to know me.
you'll find I'm not so bad.

260
00:25:07.966 --> 00:25:10.385
So. what are you. then?
Some kind of maester?

261
00:25:10.468 --> 00:25:11.678
In a manner of speaking.

262
00:25:12.220 --> 00:25:15.932
I inherited the duties
after the last one fled in the night.

263
00:25:16.015 --> 00:25:17.517
Fled? Why?

264
00:25:17.600 --> 00:25:18.935
Just never settled in.

265
00:25:21.563 --> 00:25:23.022
How are you settling in?

266
00:25:24.357 --> 00:25:27.527
I've come to know
the face of tortured rest well enough.

267
00:25:28.194 --> 00:25:29.362
Sleep can be

268
00:25:30.071 --> 00:25:31.740
thin in this place.

269
00:25:32.615 --> 00:25:34.159
What would you know of my sleep?

270
00:25:35.785 --> 00:25:38.413
Harrenhal has been cursed
since its first stone was laid.

271
00:25:40.206 --> 00:25:44.043
Black Harren felled the grove of
weirwood trees that grew on these lands.

272
00:25:44.836 --> 00:25:49.007
Heart trees. imbued with the spirits
of those who lived long before he came.

273
00:25:49.090 --> 00:25:51.301
It's said their whispers can still
be heard sometimes.

274
00:25:51.384 --> 00:25:52.844
A midwife's tale.

275
00:25:52.927 --> 00:25:56.097
Well. the very bed you sleep in
was made from such a heart tree.

276
00:25:58.141 --> 00:25:59.851
Have you experienced anything

277
00:26:00.727 --> 00:26:01.728
of note?

278
00:26:02.353 --> 00:26:04.397
You are a strange kind of woman.

279
00:26:05.356 --> 00:26:10.069
I'm no woman at all. I'm a barn owl.
Cursed to live in human form.

280
00:26:12.864 --> 00:26:14.944
So. you've come here
after quarreling with your wife.

281
00:26:15.867 --> 00:26:17.035
What?

282
00:26:18.369 --> 00:26:22.916
You arrive here alone to claim the castle
and yet send no ravens.

283
00:26:25.126 --> 00:26:27.629
Do you now plan to make your own claim?

284
00:26:28.713 --> 00:26:32.801
- Perhaps to prove yourself to her.
- Do not try me with your insolence. witch.

285
00:26:32.884 --> 00:26:34.177
It's a hard thing. I imagine.

286
00:26:34.260 --> 00:26:37.430
to give obeisance to one
who replaced you as heir.

287
00:26:40.391 --> 00:26:42.018
And a woman too.

288
00:26:42.852 --> 00:26:45.647
A girl child you bounced on your knee.

289
00:26:47.899 --> 00:26:50.735
I mean. does it please you
that her legitimacy is contested?

290
00:26:50.819 --> 00:26:54.656
As you stand here.
with a castle and a dragon.

291
00:26:55.490 --> 00:26:57.742
attempting to draw an army of men.

292
00:27:02.872 --> 00:27:03.998
Here. drink this.

293
00:27:06.417 --> 00:27:09.379
You'll need your sleep
if you're to win this place to your side.

294
00:27:19.472 --> 00:27:21.158
I rule my house as regent

295
00:27:21.182 --> 00:27:23.393
until my nephew Benjicot comes of age.

296
00:27:28.398 --> 00:27:31.442
The Brackens are venal cravens.

297
00:27:31.526 --> 00:27:34.404
They must pay for their treachery
against the laws of gods and men...

298
00:27:36.281 --> 00:27:37.407
and against the crown.

299
00:27:38.491 --> 00:27:39.826
Who are you?

300
00:27:39.909 --> 00:27:43.997
Ser Willem Blackwood of House Blackwood.
Your Grace. as I said.

301
00:27:48.418 --> 00:27:49.460
Well met.

302
00:27:50.628 --> 00:27:52.380
What might I do for you?

303
00:27:52.463 --> 00:27:55.550
It was you who summoned me. Your Grace.

304
00:27:56.676 --> 00:27:59.178
I was given to understand
that you wanted an army.

305
00:27:59.804 --> 00:28:01.598
Well. who doesn't these days?

306
00:28:01.681 --> 00:28:06.477
You Blackwoods certainly never miss
a chance to bloody your swords. do you?

307
00:28:07.770 --> 00:28:10.857
Some 20 years ago.
my lord bent the knee to King Viserys

308
00:28:10.940 --> 00:28:14.319
and acknowledged the Princess Rhaenyra
as his rightful heir.

309
00:28:14.402 --> 00:28:16.112
So you fight for this old oath.

310
00:28:16.195 --> 00:28:19.073
not for your thousand-year-old feud
with the Brackens.

311
00:28:20.783 --> 00:28:22.660
I once vied for Queen Rhaenyra's hand.

312
00:28:23.870 --> 00:28:25.330
Before she wed Ser Laenor.

313
00:28:26.414 --> 00:28:27.957
I always liked her spirit.

314
00:28:29.167 --> 00:28:31.044
She had the true blood of the dragon.

315
00:28:31.127 --> 00:28:34.756
And you're prepared to march
without the leave of your lord?

316
00:28:57.278 --> 00:28:58.404
Your Grace.

317
00:29:00.657 --> 00:29:04.953
And once you and your dragon bring
the queen's justice to the Brackens.

318
00:29:06.037 --> 00:29:07.246
our armies will be yours.

319
00:29:17.173 --> 00:29:19.717
Our lords in the Crownlands
are grousing.

320
00:29:19.801 --> 00:29:21.803
Their herds of livestock struggle
to keep pace

321
00:29:21.886 --> 00:29:24.806
with the dragons' relentless appetites...
Vhagar's in particular.

322
00:29:24.889 --> 00:29:26.992
They can either provide
the crown what it needs.

323
00:29:27.016 --> 00:29:29.185
or we can claim their holdings.

324
00:29:29.268 --> 00:29:33.022
That would be a relief. as we have
no more coin to lend to the effort.

325
00:29:33.106 --> 00:29:36.943
Resources are certainly growing no more
plentiful in the face of a blockade.

326
00:29:37.026 --> 00:29:39.380
Demand on the blacksmiths.
armorers. and tanners for equipment

327
00:29:39.404 --> 00:29:41.406
has only grown apace
with Ser Criston's army.

328
00:29:41.489 --> 00:29:43.574
Well. Cole's done splendidly.
at the least.

329
00:29:43.658 --> 00:29:47.704
turning every castle and army he's faced.
including Duskendale. gods bless him.

330
00:29:48.830 --> 00:29:50.707
Kingmaker. they're calling him.

331
00:29:50.790 --> 00:29:55.253
And with Aemond and Vhagar also at
the ready. we are a formidable opponent.

332
00:29:56.587 --> 00:29:57.714
You bore me.

333
00:30:01.092 --> 00:30:02.385
You all bore me.

334
00:30:19.278 --> 00:30:21.070
Perhaps Ser Criston will be able

335
00:30:21.154 --> 00:30:23.781
to procure more livestock
through his campaign.

336
00:30:23.865 --> 00:30:26.451
Any coin we can save will be
a welcome bounty.

337
00:30:36.419 --> 00:30:39.464
- What are you doing here?
- Where are your father's books?

338
00:30:39.547 --> 00:30:40.840
I ordered them removed.

339
00:30:41.382 --> 00:30:44.260
With no thought to the centuries
of knowledge in those pages?

340
00:30:50.933 --> 00:30:51.934
Your Grace.

341
00:30:54.145 --> 00:30:56.314
I removed them. I didn't burn them.

342
00:31:02.028 --> 00:31:05.198
- What is it?
- They don't care what I think.

343
00:31:08.534 --> 00:31:10.745
- Who. Aegon?
- My council.

344
00:31:10.828 --> 00:31:13.915
Cole. Aemond. they pursue their campaign
without seeking my aid

345
00:31:13.998 --> 00:31:15.666
or even my thoughts.

346
00:31:18.419 --> 00:31:19.754
What thoughts would you have?

347
00:31:21.380 --> 00:31:23.091
Wh... I'm the king.

348
00:31:26.511 --> 00:31:29.263
Do you think simply wearing the crown
imbues you with wisdom?

349
00:31:36.187 --> 00:31:38.773
Those men at your council table...

350
00:31:40.566 --> 00:31:41.818
earned their seats.

351
00:31:43.611 --> 00:31:46.280
It was my hope that
once enthroned.

352
00:31:46.364 --> 00:31:48.741
you would honor the burden
of your new duties.

353
00:31:48.825 --> 00:31:53.621
be silent. and strive to learn
from the more studied minds around you...

354
00:31:55.832 --> 00:31:58.192
in the hope that you might be
half the king your father was.

355
00:32:00.461 --> 00:32:02.338
- Tread carefully.
- Or what?

356
00:32:04.632 --> 00:32:07.009
You'll hang me
as you did your ratcatchers?

357
00:32:07.718 --> 00:32:09.929
Or have me banished as you did your Hand?

358
00:32:11.681 --> 00:32:15.643
I ruled in your father's absence
throughout his long illness.

359
00:32:15.726 --> 00:32:18.354
And Otto Hightower was
as cunning a statesman as ever lived.

360
00:32:18.437 --> 00:32:23.109
You should humbly be seeking
our opinions and counsel.

361
00:32:25.945 --> 00:32:29.448
You have no idea the sacrifices
that were made to put you on that throne.

362
00:32:34.829 --> 00:32:35.830
What...?

363
00:32:38.082 --> 00:32:39.876
What would you have me do. Mother?

364
00:32:42.128 --> 00:32:43.713
Do simply what is needed of you.

365
00:32:46.090 --> 00:32:47.133
Nothing.

366
00:33:17.788 --> 00:33:18.956
On your feet!

367
00:33:21.083 --> 00:33:22.335
To Rook's Rest!

368
00:33:24.170 --> 00:33:25.254
To battle!

369
00:33:30.801 --> 00:33:32.261
It's broad daylight!

370
00:33:32.845 --> 00:33:36.224
We must hold here and ready ourselves
to lay siege at nightfall.

371
00:33:36.307 --> 00:33:39.602
We shall move now and strike by day.
They will not expect it.

372
00:33:39.685 --> 00:33:43.105
They will not expect it
because it is fucking madness.

373
00:33:45.274 --> 00:33:47.944
Did you forget the little encounter
we had on the road to Rosby?

374
00:33:48.569 --> 00:33:49.570
I did not.

375
00:33:51.739 --> 00:33:54.283
Dragonstone and their dragons
are just across the bay.

376
00:33:56.077 --> 00:33:57.870
What? Grown tired of living. have you?

377
00:33:59.163 --> 00:34:00.289
Are you afraid. ser?

378
00:34:01.832 --> 00:34:04.085
Worse. I'm rational.

379
00:34:06.087 --> 00:34:07.129
We advance.

380
00:34:08.172 --> 00:34:09.172
Hyah.

381
00:34:09.173 --> 00:34:10.299
Advance!

382
00:34:28.776 --> 00:34:31.320
I see no other choice.
We need to send a dragon.

383
00:34:31.404 --> 00:34:32.405
Where?

384
00:34:37.702 --> 00:34:41.289
To support the war that your vassals
have been fighting in your absence.

385
00:34:41.872 --> 00:34:42.999
Your Grace.

386
00:34:44.583 --> 00:34:47.503
Cole's host has grown since riding abroad.

387
00:34:47.586 --> 00:34:49.797
He raised the levies
of both Rosby and Stokeworth.

388
00:34:49.880 --> 00:34:52.675
and with their combined strength.
sacked Duskendale.

389
00:34:52.758 --> 00:34:53.759
Duskendale?

390
00:34:54.427 --> 00:34:55.636
The city has fallen.

391
00:34:56.387 --> 00:35:00.266
Many Darklyn men declared for Aegon.
Those who refused were put to the sword.

392
00:35:00.349 --> 00:35:01.559
What of my father?

393
00:35:01.642 --> 00:35:03.060
He kept his oath.

394
00:35:03.936 --> 00:35:05.062
Cole took his head for it.

395
00:35:08.107 --> 00:35:13.112
Where have you been these last days?
You vanished without so much as a word.

396
00:35:14.280 --> 00:35:17.241
I apologize for my absence
and the secrecy.

397
00:35:17.325 --> 00:35:18.826
But such was necessary.

398
00:35:20.161 --> 00:35:21.495
I went to King's Landing.

399
00:35:23.205 --> 00:35:27.209
- To what possible end?
- To meet Queen Alicent and sue for peace.

400
00:35:27.293 --> 00:35:29.920
- You saw Alicent?
- Yes. I did.

401
00:35:30.004 --> 00:35:32.340
You could have been taken or slain!

402
00:35:32.423 --> 00:35:35.551
I inherited 80 years of peace
from my father.

403
00:35:36.344 --> 00:35:39.972
Before I was to end it. I needed to know
that there was no other path.

404
00:35:43.559 --> 00:35:44.560
And now I do.

405
00:35:48.230 --> 00:35:50.024
Only one choice remains to me.

406
00:35:50.816 --> 00:35:53.986
Either I win my claim or die.

407
00:35:56.530 --> 00:35:57.907
We stand at the ready.

408
00:35:59.700 --> 00:36:04.080
Cole's victories have only emboldened him.
He marches on Rook's Rest.

409
00:36:04.163 --> 00:36:07.583
His host was just hours away
when Lord Staunton's ravens took wing.

410
00:36:07.666 --> 00:36:12.421
Why Rook's Rest? After Duskendale?
It's but a small coastal keep.

411
00:36:12.505 --> 00:36:15.216
Because Lord Staunton
is a member of this council.

412
00:36:16.300 --> 00:36:19.595
And because his castle is small
and vulnerable and there for the taking.

413
00:36:20.262 --> 00:36:23.099
Cole knows we have no army
on the mainland.

414
00:36:23.182 --> 00:36:25.226
- He is brazen.
- He is daring us to act.

415
00:36:25.309 --> 00:36:27.436
We need to send a dragon.

416
00:36:35.236 --> 00:36:38.614
There are those who have mistaken
my caution for weakness.

417
00:36:43.744 --> 00:36:45.079
Let that be their undoing.

418
00:36:46.622 --> 00:36:48.457
- I will go.
- My queen...

419
00:36:49.083 --> 00:36:51.710
- You cannot.
- I will not loose dragons to war

420
00:36:51.794 --> 00:36:53.212
whilst I hide here in my castle.

421
00:36:53.295 --> 00:36:56.298
Our allies raise
their banners for you. Mother.

422
00:36:56.382 --> 00:36:57.383
Yes. they do.

423
00:36:58.426 --> 00:37:02.388
- If you die. all is lost! Send me.
- No.

424
00:37:02.471 --> 00:37:05.099
I will burn Cole's lines and withdraw
before King's Landing

425
00:37:05.182 --> 00:37:07.102
- can raise the alarm.
- You lack the experience.

426
00:37:09.937 --> 00:37:12.857
You must send me. Your Grace.

427
00:37:14.442 --> 00:37:17.361
Meleys is your largest dragon
and no stranger to battle.

428
00:37:20.781 --> 00:37:22.116
I will meet Cole.

429
00:38:31.435 --> 00:38:35.606
I wish only to fight for you.
for your claim and mine. I...

430
00:38:38.025 --> 00:38:39.705
There's something
I need to tell you. Jace.

431
00:38:42.196 --> 00:38:45.658
Something I should have told you

432
00:38:45.741 --> 00:38:47.910
when you first became heir to the throne.

433
00:38:49.119 --> 00:38:53.624
<i>It's a secret that Viserys told me
when he named me his successor.</i>

434
00:38:55.334 --> 00:38:58.087
<i>And it has passed from king to heir</i>

435
00:38:59.213 --> 00:39:01.423
<i>since Aegon the Conqueror's time.</i>

436
00:39:10.224 --> 00:39:14.186
<i>I never told you because
I was unsure that I believed it myself.</i>

437
00:39:15.604 --> 00:39:18.482
<i>The Targaryen who sits the Iron Throne</i>

438
00:39:19.525 --> 00:39:21.151
<i>is notjust a king or a queen.</i>

439
00:39:21.944 --> 00:39:23.654
<i>They are a protector.</i>

440
00:39:27.783 --> 00:39:31.787
<i>Ordained to lead the Seven
Kingdoms. to strengthen them...</i>

441
00:39:34.331 --> 00:39:38.085
<i>...and to unite them against a common foe.</i>

442
00:39:39.753 --> 00:39:41.005
Ready!

443
00:39:42.756 --> 00:39:45.634
<i>Viserys chose me to succeed him.</i>

444
00:39:47.094 --> 00:39:49.388
<i>He held to this the whole of his life.</i>

445
00:39:55.311 --> 00:40:00.608
<i>My father believed that I alone
was meant to be this protector.</i>

446
00:40:01.650 --> 00:40:04.486
They're 14. 1500 strong at least. my lord.

447
00:40:06.155 --> 00:40:09.617
<i>But to unite the realm.
I had to send the dragons to war.</i>

448
00:40:18.542 --> 00:40:21.629
The horrors I have just loosed
cannot be for a crown alone.

449
00:40:24.173 --> 00:40:28.677
<i>That is why I must believe what
Viserys told me when he named me his heir.</i>

450
00:40:29.470 --> 00:40:31.221
<i>What Jaehaerys had told him.</i>

451
00:40:32.598 --> 00:40:34.433
<i>And what I will now tell you.</i>

452
00:40:37.645 --> 00:40:38.729
What is it?

453
00:40:45.027 --> 00:40:47.071
Aegon the Conqueror's Dream.

454
00:40:49.573 --> 00:40:52.660
He called it the Song of Ice and Fire.

455
00:41:02.878 --> 00:41:03.921
Loose!

456
00:41:04.004 --> 00:41:05.005
New rank!

457
00:41:06.548 --> 00:41:07.549
Loose!

458
00:41:08.258 --> 00:41:10.886
Next rank! Loose!

459
00:41:17.559 --> 00:41:18.811
Push it!

460
00:41:19.436 --> 00:41:21.230
- Dragon!
- Dragon!

461
00:41:21.855 --> 00:41:22.940
Dragon!

462
00:41:27.444 --> 00:41:29.822
To the Seven Hells
with you. Cole!

463
00:41:30.489 --> 00:41:32.770
You may as well have sounded horns
to announce our coming.

464
00:41:32.825 --> 00:41:34.886
Order the Darklyn levies
to break off and move ahead.

465
00:41:34.910 --> 00:41:36.745
We must keep
the dragon's attention divided.

466
00:41:36.829 --> 00:41:38.789
- Make the signal.
- What signal?

467
00:41:38.872 --> 00:41:40.249
All is going to plan.

468
00:43:12.883 --> 00:43:14.468
Forward. Sunfyre!

469
00:43:14.551 --> 00:43:16.595
Faster!

470
00:43:17.304 --> 00:43:19.306
- Dragon!
- Dragon!

471
00:43:19.389 --> 00:43:20.516
Whose dragon is that?

472
00:43:21.391 --> 00:43:22.726
His Grace. the king's.

473
00:43:24.144 --> 00:43:26.313
This was your secret plot. Cole?

474
00:43:26.396 --> 00:43:29.525
For the king himself to lay ambush
and mayhaps die in the attempt?

475
00:43:29.608 --> 00:43:32.319
No! Loose more signal arrows!

476
00:43:32.402 --> 00:43:34.279
Signal arrows!

477
00:43:35.739 --> 00:43:41.286
Stalwart men of House Targaryen.
your king has joined you!

478
00:43:42.788 --> 00:43:44.122
Hold to your courage!

479
00:43:44.206 --> 00:43:45.415
Hold to your wits!

480
00:43:45.499 --> 00:43:50.671
For the Seven have blessed and shielded
this host with divine purpose!

481
00:43:50.754 --> 00:43:56.218
For the one true king. Aegon! Advance!

482
00:44:04.518 --> 00:44:05.853
Where are you. Aemond?

483
00:44:21.660 --> 00:44:22.995
<i>Dracarys!</i>

484
00:44:42.973 --> 00:44:44.474
Ahh!

485
00:45:01.950 --> 00:45:03.201
Another one there!

486
00:45:04.077 --> 00:45:07.956
Send a volley to those Rosby men!
Give them no quarter!

487
00:45:17.674 --> 00:45:19.426
We'd best get you to cover. my lord.

488
00:46:08.433 --> 00:46:09.768
Thank the gods!

489
00:46:11.895 --> 00:46:13.105
<i>Dracarys!</i>

490
00:46:18.610 --> 00:46:20.737
No! No!

491
00:46:40.173 --> 00:46:41.383
Your Grace!

492
00:51:48.148 --> 00:51:49.607
Fall in behind me!

493
00:51:51.276 --> 00:51:52.652
Into the breach!

494
00:52:24.768 --> 00:52:27.312
The king has fallen. We must find him.

495
00:53:17.529 --> 00:53:18.530
Aemond!

496
00:53:34.170 --> 00:53:35.338
Where is His Grace?
